In the tall grass of South America struts a walking enigma. Long-legged, flame-colored, and always alone but never lonely, it looks the part of a dog from hell. It looks like a fox, walks like a deer, and, of course, howls like a… banshee from your worst nightmare. This isn't the furry version of slenderman, it's a very real canid. This is the maned wolf.

The Andean Cat is the rarest and most endangered cat in the world. It lives at the top of fragmented mountain ranges and has a very selective diet. Very few people have ever seen it. Its coat blends in with the rocks. Its long tail and legs help it navigate the rocks with perfect stealth and it prefers to move under the cover of darkness.
